---
const questions = [
  {
    id: 'faq-1',
    title: 'What services does your property management company offer to landlords?',
    answer:
      'Our property management services encompass a range of offerings, including letting services to help landlords find suitable tenants, as well as property development services to enhance the value and appeal of your investment.',
  },
  {
    id: 'faq-2',
    title: 'How can I benefit from your letting services?',
    answer:
      'Our letting services are designed to streamline the process of finding and securing reliable tenants for your property. We handle tenant screening, property marketing, and lease agreements to ensure a hassle-free experience for landlords.',
  },
  {
    id: 'faq-3',
    title: 'What does your property development service include?',
    answer:
      'Our property development service focuses on optimizing the value of your property. This may involve renovations, upgrades, or strategic enhancements to attract higher-quality tenants and increase the overall market value of your investment.',
  },
  {
    id: 'faq-4',
    title: 'How do you market and advertise rental properties?',
    answer:
      'We employ a multi-faceted approach to market and advertise rental properties. This includes online listings, social media promotion, and collaboration with local real estate networks to maximize visibility and attract potential tenants.',
  },
  {
    id: 'faq-5',
    title: 'Can you assist with tenant screening and selection?',
    answer:
      'Yes, our property management team conducts thorough tenant screening processes, which typically involve credit checks, rental history verification, and references. We aim to place reliable and responsible tenants in your property.',
  },
  {
    id: 'faq-6',
    title: 'How are property maintenance and repairs handled?',
    answer:
      'We have a network of trusted maintenance professionals to address any issues promptly. Landlords can rely on us to coordinate and oversee routine maintenance and repairs, ensuring that the property is well-maintained and tenants are satisfied.',
  },
  {
    id: 'faq-7',
    title: 'What fees are associated with your property management services?',
    answer:
      'Our fee structure varies based on the specific services you require. We offer transparent pricing, and our team will discuss all associated fees, including letting and property development services, during the initial consultation.',
  },
  {
    id: 'faq-8',
    title: 'How do I get started with your property management services?',
    answer:
      'To get started, simply contact us through our website or give us a call. We\'ll schedule a consultation to understand your specific needs and discuss how our services can benefit you as a landlord.',
  },
  {
    id: 'faq-9',
    title: 'Do you handle legal aspects such as lease agreements and eviction procedures?',
    answer:
      'Yes, we assist landlords in drafting and managing lease agreements. In the unfortunate event of eviction, we provide guidance and support throughout the legal process to protect your interests and ensure compliance with local regulations.',
  },
  {
    id: 'faq-10',
    title: 'How can I track the performance of my rental property?',
    answer:
      'Our property management platform provides landlords with access to real-time performance metrics, financial statements, and relevant documentation. This allows you to stay informed and make data-driven decisions about your investment.',
  },
];

---

<section class="py-16 sm:py-20">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:max-w-7xl lg:px-8">
    <div class="grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-3 lg:gap-8">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-medium tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">Frequently asked questions</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="lg:col-span-2">
        <dl
          class="-mt-3"
          x-data="{ selected: null, toggle(value) { this.selected = this.selected === value ? null : value } }"
        >
          {
            questions.map((question, index) => (
              <div
                class="rounded-3xl px-4 transition"
                x-data={`{ id: ${index}, get isOpen() { return this.id === this.selected }, get isNextOpen() { return (this.id + 1) === this.selected } }`}
                x-bind:class="{ 'bg-primary-500/10 dark:bg-primary-400/10': isOpen }"
              >
                <dt
                  class="border-b text-lg transition"
                  x-cloak
                  x-bind:class="{ 'border-transparent': isOpen || isNextOpen, 'border-primary-900/10 dark:border-primary-300/10': !(isOpen || isNextOpen) }"
                >
                  <button
                    type="button"
                    class="group block w-full py-6 text-left transition focus-visible:outline-none"
                    aria-controls={question.id}
                    x-on:click="toggle(id)"
                    aria-expanded="false"
                    x-bind:aria-expanded="isOpen.toString()"
                  >
                    <div class="group-focus-visible:outline-primary-950 dark:group-focus-visible:outline-primary-200 flex items-center justify-between rounded-3xl group-focus-visible:outline group-focus-visible:outline-2 group-focus-visible:outline-offset-2">
                      <span class="font-medium">{question.title}</span>
                      <span class="ml-6 flex h-7 items-center">
                        <svg
                          class="text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 h-6 w-6 rotate-0 transform transition duration-200 ease-in-out"
                          x-bind:class="{ '-rotate-180': isOpen, 'rotate-0': !isOpen }"
                          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                          viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                          fill="currentColor"
                          aria-hidden="true"
                        >
                          <path d="M11.9997 13.1714L16.9495 8.22168L18.3637 9.63589L11.9997 15.9999L5.63574 9.63589L7.04996 8.22168L11.9997 13.1714Z" />
                        </svg>
                      </span>
                    </div>
                  </button>
                </dt>
                <dd class="pb-6 pr-6" id={question.id} x-show="isOpen" x-cloak x-collapse>
                  <p class="text-primary-950/70 dark:text-primary-200/70 text-base">
                    {question.answer}
                  </p>
                </dd>
              </div>
            ))
          }
        </dl>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
